This paper deals with training deep directed graphical models, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper proposes a novel interpretation of the wake-sleep algorithm, which is a popular method for training such models. The paper also discusses the use of powerful layer models such as NADE for the inference network. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
